<Window x:Class="MissionEditor2.Help"
    xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
    Title="Help" SizeToContent="WidthAndHeight" WindowStyle="ToolWindow" ResizeMode="NoResize">
    <StackPanel>
        <TextBlock Padding="5" TextWrapping="WrapWithOverflow">
            Triggers are containers that bind actions and conditions together. 
            <LineBreak/> 
            When any of the conditons are met, all actions in the trigger take place. 
            <LineBreak/> 
            Help for individual actions and conditions can be found in their configuration pages.
            <LineBreak/>
            You can access trigger settings by right-clicking on them.
            <LineBreak />
            Delete triggers, conditions or actions by right-clicking on them and selecting "Delete".
            <LineBreak />
            Drag dock panels by the header bar to dock them in other positions.
            <LineBreak />
            <LineBreak />
            Join #sp for help!
        </TextBlock>
        <Button IsCancel="True" HorizontalAlignment="Right" Width="50" Margin="3" >OK</Button>
    </StackPanel>
</Window>
